The paper deals with image analysis, specifically in the context of hyperspectral image interpretation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes a unified framework for classification and low-level modeling, which involves the use of latent variables and supervised information. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of clustering, which suggests that it may belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the interpretation of images, which suggests that it may also belong to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
